      • skip

        public void skip(FastBufferedInputStream is)
          throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: ByteSerializerDeserializer
        Skip an object, usually without deserializing it.

        Note that this method requires explicitly a FastBufferedInputStream. As a result, you can safely use skip() to skip the number of bytes required (see the documentation of FastBufferedInputStream.skip(long) for some elaboration).

        Calling this method must be equivalent to calling ByteSerializerDeserializer.fromStream(InputStream) and discarding the result.

        Specified by:
        skip in interface ByteSerializerDeserializer<CharSequence>
        Parameters:
        is - the fast buffered input stream from which the next object will be skipped.
        Throws:
        IOException
